# 🏗️ CORE PROJECT CONTEXT & STACK

**Project**: Trip Planner - Multi-day trip planning application with interactive map
**Framework**: Vite + React 18 + TypeScript
**Design System**: IBM Carbon Design System v11
**Styling**: Carbon Components (@carbon/react) + Carbon tokens + SCSS
**Map**: Leaflet + React Leaflet
**Backend**: Firebase (Firestore, Authentication)
**State**: React Context API + Local State
**Drag & Drop**: @dnd-kit/core

---

# 🎨 CARBON DESIGN SYSTEM MASTERY

## 1️⃣ COMPONENT SELECTION & USAGE

### Always Use Carbon Components First
✅ **DO**: Use Carbon components from `@carbon/react`
❌ **DON'T**: Create custom buttons, inputs, modals, or form elements

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Button, TextInput, Modal, Loading } from '@carbon/react';

// ❌ WRONG
const CustomButton = () => <button className="my-button">...</button>;
```

### Carbon Component Catalog
| Need | Carbon Component | Import |
|------|------------------|--------|
| Button | `<Button>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Text Input | `<TextInput>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Select Dropdown | `<Select>`, `<SelectItem>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Modal | `<Modal>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Notification | `<InlineNotification>`, `<ToastNotification>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Loading | `<Loading>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Tabs | `<Tabs>`, `<TabList>`, `<Tab>`, `<TabPanels>`, `<TabPanel>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Toggle | `<Toggle>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Checkbox | `<Checkbox>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Radio | `<RadioButton>`, `<RadioButtonGroup>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Menu | `<OverflowMenu>`, `<OverflowMenuItem>` | `@carbon/react` |
| Grid | `<Grid>`, `<Column>` | `@carbon/react` |

---

## 2️⃣ BUTTON STATES & VARIANTS

### Complete Button Implementation
Every button MUST handle all states:

```typescript
<Button
  kind="primary"           // primary | secondary | tertiary | ghost | danger
  size="md"               // sm | md | lg | xl | 2xl
  disabled={isSubmitting} // Disabled state
  renderIcon={Add}        // Optional icon (from @carbon/icons-react)
  iconDescription="Add"   // Required if renderIcon is used
  onClick={handleClick}
>
  {isSubmitting ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}
</Button>
```

### Button Hierarchy Rules
1. **Primary**: Main CTA (max 1 per screen section)
2. **Secondary**: Alternative actions
3. **Tertiary**: Less important actions
4. **Ghost**: Minimal visual weight (e.g., "Cancel")
5. **Danger**: Destructive actions (delete, remove)

---

## 3️⃣ FORM COMPONENTS - COMPLETE STATES

### TextInput - All States
```typescript
<TextInput
  id="location-name"
  labelText="Location name"          // Always include label
  placeholder="Enter location name"   // Helpful placeholder
  value={formData.name}
  onChange={(e) => handleChange('name', e.target.value)}
  invalid={!!errors.name}            // Error state
  invalidText={errors.name}          // Error message
  disabled={isSubmitting}            // Disabled state
  helperText="This will appear on the map" // Optional help text
  required                           // Visual indicator
/>
```

### Select - All States
```typescript
<Select
  id="category"
  labelText="Category"
  value={formData.category}
  onChange={(e) => handleChange('category', e.target.value)}
  invalid={!!errors.category}
  invalidText={errors.category}
  disabled={isSubmitting}
  helperText="Choose the type of location"
>
  <SelectItem value="" text="Choose category" />
  {CATEGORIES.map((cat) => (
    <SelectItem key={cat.value} value={cat.value} text={cat.label} />
  ))}
</Select>
```

### Form Group Pattern
```typescript
<FormGroup legendText="Basic Information">
  <Stack gap={5}>
    <TextInput {...props} />
    <Select {...props} />
  </Stack>
</FormGroup>
```

---

## 4️⃣ MODAL PATTERNS

### Complete Modal Implementation
```typescript
<Modal
  open={isOpen}
  onRequestClose={handleClose}
  modalHeading="Add Location"
  modalLabel="Trip Planning"              // Optional category label
  primaryButtonText={isEditing ? "Update" : "Add"}
  secondaryButtonText="Cancel"
  primaryButtonDisabled={isSubmitting || !isValid}
  onRequestSubmit={handleSubmit}
  preventCloseOnClickOutside={hasUnsavedChanges}
  size="md"                              // xs | sm | md | lg
>
  {isSubmitting && (
    <Loading description="Saving..." withOverlay={false} />
  )}
  <Stack gap={6}>
    {/* Form content */}
  </Stack>
</Modal>
```

### Modal UX Rules
1. **Always provide** both primary and secondary actions
2. **Disable primary button** when form is invalid or submitting
3. **Show loading state** during async operations
4. **Prevent close** if there are unsaved changes (with confirmation)
5. **Focus management**: First input gets focus on open
6. **Escape key**: Should close modal (unless prevented)

---

## 5️⃣ LOADING STATES

### Never Show Text-Only Loading
❌ **WRONG**: `<p>Loading...</p>`
✅ **CORRECT**: Use Carbon Loading component

```typescript
// Full-page loading
<div style={{ 
  height: '100%', 
  display: 'flex', 
  alignItems: 'center', 
  justifyContent: 'center' 
}}>
  <Loading description="Loading trip plan..." withOverlay={false} />
</div>

// Inline loading (small)
<Loading description="Loading..." withOverlay={false} small />

// Button loading state
<Button disabled={isLoading}>
  {isLoading ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}
</Button>
```

---

## 6️⃣ NOTIFICATION PATTERNS

### InlineNotification - For Contextual Feedback
```typescript
<InlineNotification
  kind="error"              // error | warning | info | success
  title="Error"
  subtitle={error}
  onClose={() => setError(null)}  // Always dismissible
  lowContrast={false}       // Use high contrast for errors
  hideCloseButton={false}   // Allow dismissal
/>
```

### ToastNotification - For Global Feedback
```typescript
<ToastNotification
  kind="success"
  title="Location added"
  subtitle="Your location has been saved to Day 1"
  timeout={3000}            // Auto-dismiss after 3s
  onClose={() => {}}
/>
```

### Notification Hierarchy
1. **Error**: Always high contrast, dismissible, stays until dismissed
2. **Warning**: Medium priority, auto-dismiss after 5s
3. **Success**: Low priority, auto-dismiss after 3s
4. **Info**: Contextual, auto-dismiss after 4s

---

## 7️⃣ SPACING & LAYOUT TOKENS

### Carbon Spacing Scale
Use Carbon spacing tokens instead of arbitrary values:

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `$spacing-02` | 0.25rem (4px) | Minimal spacing |
| `$spacing-03` | 0.5rem (8px) | Tight spacing |
| `$spacing-04` | 0.75rem (12px) | Default inline spacing |
| `$spacing-05` | 1rem (16px) | Standard spacing |
| `$spacing-06` | 1.5rem (24px) | Section spacing |
| `$spacing-07` | 2rem (32px) | Large spacing |
| `$spacing-09` | 3rem (48px) | XL spacing |

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Using Carbon tokens
<div style={{ padding: '1rem', gap: '1rem' }}>  // $spacing-05

// ❌ WRONG - Arbitrary values
<div style={{ padding: '13px', gap: '17px' }}>
```

### Stack Component Pattern
```typescript
import { Stack } from '@carbon/react';

<Stack gap={5}>  {/* gap uses spacing scale: 5 = $spacing-05 */}
  <TextInput {...props} />
  <Select {...props} />
</Stack>
```

---

## 8️⃣ COLOR TOKENS

### Always Use Carbon Color Tokens
```scss
// ✅ CORRECT - Carbon tokens
.sidebar {
  background-color: $layer-01;
  border-right: 1px solid $border-subtle;
  color: $text-primary;
}

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
.sidebar {
  background-color: #ffffff;
  border-right: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  color: #161616;
}
```

### Common Color Tokens
| Token | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `$layer-01` | Primary background |
| `$layer-02` | Secondary background (cards) |
| `$layer-accent-01` | Accent background |
| `$text-primary` | Primary text |
| `$text-secondary` | Secondary text |
| `$text-placeholder` | Placeholder text |
| `$border-subtle` | Subtle borders |
| `$border-strong` | Prominent borders |
| `$interactive-01` | Primary interactive color |
| `$interactive-02` | Secondary interactive color |
| `$danger` | Error/destructive actions |

