# 🎯 STAFF-LEVEL UX/UI PRINCIPLES

## 1️⃣ VISUAL HIERARCHY

### Information Architecture
1. **Primary Actions**: High visual weight (primary buttons, large text)
2. **Secondary Actions**: Medium weight (secondary buttons, body text)
3. **Tertiary Actions**: Low weight (ghost buttons, caption text)

### Typography Scale
```typescript
// Page Title
<h1 style={{ fontSize: '2rem', fontWeight: 600 }}>Trip Planner</h1>

// Section Heading
<h2 style={{ fontSize: '1.5rem', fontWeight: 600 }}>Day 1</h2>

// Subsection
<h3 style={{ fontSize: '1.25rem', fontWeight: 600 }}>Locations</h3>

// Body
<p style={{ fontSize: '1rem', lineHeight: 1.5 }}>Description text</p>

// Caption
<span style={{ fontSize: '0.875rem', color: '$text-secondary' }}>Helper text</span>
```

---

## 2️⃣ INTERACTION DESIGN

### Micro-interactions Checklist
- [ ] **Hover states**: All interactive elements have visible hover
- [ ] **Active states**: Click/tap feedback
- [ ] **Focus states**: Keyboard navigation visible (focus rings)
- [ ] **Disabled states**: Visually distinct, cursor not-allowed
- [ ] **Loading states**: Clear feedback during async operations
- [ ] **Error states**: Clear, actionable error messages
- [ ] **Empty states**: Helpful guidance when no data

### Transition Standards
```scss
// Standard transition
transition: all 200ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.38, 0.9); // Carbon motion

// Hover effect
.card {
  transition: transform 200ms, box-shadow 200ms;
  
  &:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }
}
```

---

## 3️⃣ FEEDBACK & COMMUNICATION

### Every Action Needs Feedback
| Action | Feedback |
|--------|----------|
| Create | Success notification + UI update |
| Update | Success notification + UI update |
| Delete | Confirmation modal → Success notification |
| Error | Error notification with retry action |
| Loading | Loading spinner/skeleton |
| Empty state | Helpful message with CTA |

### Error Message Quality
❌ **BAD**: "Error occurred"
✅ **GOOD**: "Unable to save location. Please check your connection and try again."

```typescript
// Error handling pattern
try {
  await createLocation(data);
  showNotification('success', 'Location added successfully');
} catch (error) {
  showNotification(
    'error',
    'Unable to add location',
    error.message || 'Please check your connection and try again'
  );
}
```

---

## 4️⃣ ACCESSIBILITY (A11Y) REQUIREMENTS

### Non-Negotiable A11Y Rules
1. ✅ **All images have alt text** (or empty alt="" if decorative)
2. ✅ **All form inputs have labels** (visible or aria-label)
3. ✅ **Color is not the only indicator** (use icons + text)
4. ✅ **Keyboard navigation works** (tab, enter, escape)
5. ✅ **Focus is visible** (focus rings on interactive elements)
6. ✅ **ARIA labels for icon buttons**
7. ✅ **Semantic HTML** (button for actions, a for links)

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Accessible icon button
<Button
  kind="ghost"
  renderIcon={Edit}
  iconDescription="Edit location"
  hasIconOnly
  onClick={handleEdit}
/>

// ❌ WRONG - Not accessible
<div onClick={handleEdit}>
  <Edit />
</div>
```

---

## 5️⃣ RESPONSIVE DESIGN

### Mobile-First Approach
1. Design for mobile first (320px+)
2. Add complexity for tablet (768px+)
3. Optimize for desktop (1024px+)

### Breakpoint Strategy
```scss
// Mobile (default)
.sidebar {
  width: 100%;
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 0;
}

// Tablet
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .sidebar {
    width: 320px;
    position: relative;
  }
}

// Desktop
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .sidebar {
    width: 360px;
  }
}
```

---

## 6️⃣ PERFORMANCE & OPTIMIZATION

### Performance Checklist
- [ ] **Lazy load** heavy components (map, modals)
- [ ] **Debounce** search inputs (300ms)
- [ ] **Throttle** scroll handlers
- [ ] **Memoize** expensive calculations (useMemo)
- [ ] **Optimize images** (WebP, lazy loading)
- [ ] **Code splitting** (React.lazy + Suspense)

```typescript
// Debounced search
const debouncedSearch = useMemo(
  () => debounce((value: string) => {
    performSearch(value);
  }, 300),
  []
);
```

---

# 🔥 FIREBASE PATTERNS

## Security First
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS check authentication
if (!user) {
  throw new Error('User must be authenticated');
}

// ✅ ALWAYS set userId
await createTripPlan({
  ...data,
  userId: user.uid,  // Critical!
  createdAt: serverTimestamp(),
  updatedAt: serverTimestamp(),
});
```

## Optimistic Updates
```typescript
// 1. Update UI immediately
setLocations(prev => [...prev, newLocation]);

// 2. Update Firestore
try {
  await createLocation(planId, dayId, newLocation);
} catch (error) {
  // 3. Rollback on error
  setLocations(prev => prev.filter(l => l.id !== newLocation.id));
  showError(error);
}
```

---

# 🗺️ MAP-SPECIFIC PATTERNS

## Leaflet + Carbon Integration
```typescript
// Custom marker with Carbon colors
const customIcon = L.divIcon({
  html: `<div style="color: ${dayColor}">
    ${renderToString(<LocationPin />)}
  </div>`,
  className: 'custom-marker',
  iconSize: [32, 32],
});
```

## Map Performance
- **Cluster markers** when > 50 locations
- **Debounce zoom** events
- **Lazy load** route polylines
- **Memoize** marker positions

