# 🚫 ANTI-PATTERNS (Never Do This)

## 1. Don't Mix Design Systems
❌ **WRONG**: Using Tailwind classes in Carbon project
```typescript
<Button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500">  // NO!
```

## 2. Don't Create Custom Basic Components
❌ **WRONG**: Custom button when Carbon has one
```typescript
const MyButton = () => <button>...</button>  // NO!
```

## 3. Don't Hardcode Colors
❌ **WRONG**: Using hex colors
```scss
color: #161616;  // NO!
```
✅ **CORRECT**: Using tokens
```scss
color: $text-primary;  // YES!
```

## 4. Don't Skip Loading States
❌ **WRONG**: No feedback during async operations
```typescript
onClick={async () => {
  await saveData();  // User sees nothing happening
}}
```

## 5. Don't Ignore Errors Silently
❌ **WRONG**: Swallowing errors
```typescript
try {
  await saveData();
} catch (error) {
  // silence is not golden
}
```

## 6. Don't Use Inline Styles for Everything
❌ **WRONG**: Complex inline styles
```typescript
<div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '16px', padding: '24px' }}>
```
✅ **CORRECT**: Use SCSS modules or Carbon components
```typescript
<Stack gap={6} className="container">
```

---

# 🎯 DEFINITION OF DONE

A feature is DONE when:
- [ ] ✅ Uses Carbon Design System components
- [ ] ✅ All interactive states implemented (hover, focus, active, disabled)
- [ ] ✅ All async states implemented (loading, error, success, empty)
- [ ] ✅ TypeScript types defined (no `any`)
- [ ] ✅ Accessible (keyboard nav, ARIA labels, focus management)
- [ ] ✅ Responsive (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- [ ] ✅ Loading feedback with Carbon `<Loading>`
- [ ] ✅ Error handling with `<InlineNotification>`
- [ ] ✅ Firebase operations include auth checks
- [ ] ✅ No console errors or warnings
- [ ] ✅ Smooth transitions (200ms Carbon motion)
- [ ] ✅ Performance optimized (memoization, debouncing)
- [ ] ✅ Empty states with helpful guidance
- [ ] ✅ Success feedback for user actions
- [ ] ✅ Code is documented (complex logic explained)

---

# 🏆 EXCELLENCE MINDSET

> "Every component is an opportunity to delight the user."

1. **Sweat the details**: 2px can make a difference
2. **Anticipate needs**: Empty states guide next actions
3. **Communicate clearly**: Users should never wonder "what's happening?"
4. **Be consistent**: Same action, same pattern, everywhere
5. **Performance matters**: Every 100ms counts
6. **Accessibility is not optional**: Everyone deserves great UX

